headlines.description: Goals from Paulo Dybala and Juan Cuadrado sent Juventus back to the top of the Serie A table with a 2-0 win over 10-man Brescia on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No Ronaldo, no problem as Juventus win

headlines.description: A stunning finish from Dries Mertens earned Napoli a 1-0 win at Cagliari that moved them above the Sardinian side and into eighth place in Serie A.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mertens curler earns Napoli narrow win at Cagliari

headlines.description: Lazio mounted a superb second-half comeback at the Olympic Stadium to beat Inter Milan 2-1 and move above Antonio Conte's side into second place.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lazio leapfrog into 2nd place with win over Inter
